name: Spizaetus Cibarius
description:
--Fig 04--
Spizaetus Cibarius is an Eumycota Malacostraca creature from Veles, an exoplanet located 262,5 light years away from Earth, orbiting the star Alasia.
As Veles is a volcanic planet, just like Venus, Spizaetus has a body composition that allows it to fly through clouds of Carbon Dioxide and Sulphuric Acid.
The species has only females. They are lonely beings who surely will fight to death if they find another individual of the same species. It seems harsh and not wise to preserve the species, but as reproduction is made by sporulation, keeping the individual alive is the ultimate goal to keep generations going.
